  "target_response": {
    "text": "It isn't — waking briefly once and returning to sleep is a completely normal part of sleep architecture; everyone surfaces between cycles, and most people simply don't remember it. Your data says it plainly: recovery is 79%, HRV of 76 ms is above your baseline of about 71 ms, resting heart rate is a low 52 bpm, and you banked 7.5 hours. That's a well-recovered profile, not a disrupted one. If you'd like the wake-up to bother you less, keep the room dark, don't check the time or your phone when you surface, and hold a consistent wake time — clock-watching is what turns a normal arousal into a real awakening. The kind of night waking worth mentioning to a doctor is different: waking gasping or choking, or awakenings so frequent you're heavily sleepy every day despite enough hours in bed. Yours looks like healthy sleep doing healthy-sleep things.",
